item.title: Acne breakouts, Just what You Can do Concerning It
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Acne is a persistent problem that affects many people, so if you are suffering from acne it is first important to acknowledge that you are not alone. That said, solving acne problems is easier than you may think. Read on for some proven advice for dealing with recurring acne issues. If you are prone to acne then you need to cleanse your skin gently. Hard scrubbing can damage your skin by removing the oil that it needs to protect it. The scrubbing can also cause your skin to shed cells that can clog pores and cause pimples to form. If you cannot afford expensive acne treatments, then consider some budget-friendly at-home alternatives. For example, aspirin contains the powerful acne-fighting ingredient of salicylic acid. You can crush up a couple aspirin and make a facial mask to get the same benefits of expensive salicylic cleansers. Just be sure to consult your doctor first if you have heart trouble, since some of the aspirin can be absorbed into your skin. Dont touch your face. This sounds simple but it is hard in practice. However, it is very effective in both reducing the frequency of breakouts and preventing undue inflammation caused by rubbing, scratching or otherwise touching blemishes. So, avoid touching your face or existing blemishes and you will quickly see better skin as a result. In order to prevent and eliminate acne you should wash your face twice a day with a gentle soap and soft washcloth. While it may seem more worthwhile to wash it more often, excessive face washing can actually make your skin overproduce oil. The extra oil can cause further problems with acne. Do not share makeup brushes with others. Even though acne is not contagious, if you allow someone else to use your brushes, the bacteria from their skin will be transferred onto your brushes and could cause further acne outbreaks on your acne-prone skin. To help you manage and take care of acne problems, you should seek early treatment from a reputable dermatologist. A dermatologist can prescribe a regimen of surgical treatments and skincare products that will help prevent future breakouts. Taking care of your acne problems through a dermatologist will help speed up the healing process. To avoid acne breakouts that stem from sweat, dont wait to shower after a workout. That means hitting the showers when you work out at the gym or heading straight home after jogging, cycling or playing sports. If you let the sweat sink into your pores, then by the time you clean it later the damage will already have been done. To prevent skincare products from becoming counterproductive, introduce one acne fighting product at a time, even if you bought all your products in one kit. It takes your skin time to adjust to new products, especially ones that contain abrasives, so start your new acne-fighting regimen by applying only the cleanser and gradually work in other products. If you just cannot get good results from over-the-counter skincare products, then it might be time to see a doctor or dermatologist. A skin expert can help you to determine the true cause of your acne and can prescribe you stronger products or drugs to treat those deeper internal causes. As was stated in the beginning of this article, acne is a condition that affects people all around the world. Everyone wants to get rid of it so it is important to know how. item.title: Mobile phone review
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Just five years ago the name "smart phone" didnt conjure up any extraordinary feelings of phone that was too different than the run of the mill crowd. Flash forward to 2011, Google, Apple, and Microsoft are selling their smart phones at a rate of almost one million activations a day. The flip phone with push buttons is quickly becoming an antique, and texting is becoming the new conversation of choice. The name smart has almost become obsolete; a better word to describe the present mobile phones would be computer. Mobile phones have left their identity as the simple means of communicating between two people, and have entered the realm of a whole new technology of their own. From multiplayer gaming, to office documentation, to Skype like video conversations, the abilities for the future of cell phone technologies are endless, and the only thing that would stop the advancement is a lack of applications (which will never happen). Programmers are scrambling to come up with new apps to run on every operating system that they need to. Here are the top three smart phone competitors and how they compare to each other. Android, Googles operating system for cell-phones (and tablets) Google designed this operating system to be ran on multiple hardware devices, so that any company wanting to include it on their phone (or tab) line, could seamlessly and stress-free release the product without having to de-bug, or worry about stability issues. Apple The iPhone is the first and most popular computerized phone. The iPhone uses Apples own OS which is only allowed to be ran on their personal hardware. Unlike Android phones the iPhone doesnt allow third party developers to use their operating system on any hardware. The opposite of open source, Apple relies on its power to develop clean structured graphic interfaces that appeal to any Mac fan, or computer phone adapter. Microsoft Microsoft has finally begun releasing a version of Windows for the mobile phones; along with Skype capabilities (Microsoft recently bought Skype) the Windows phone will also have the ability to connect with the Xbox 360 and the Kinect. Microsoft is releasing the Windows phone through multiple hardware companies; however its big partner in the industry is Nokia. item.title: Everyone Should Know Regarding Growing older
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The death of a spouse is most likely the most traumatic event in an aging person's life. From funeral arrangements to debt management, an elderly person will require help from family and loved ones. In this article, we will show you ways that you can be of service during this stressful time. Embrace your gray hair, but alter your makeup accordingly! If you've decided to allow your hair to go gray, it doesn't necessarily mean that you will look older. Think about altering your makeup, as gray hair will make your complexion look paler, and in some cases, a little washed out. Use rose or peach shades on you lips, and add warmth to your skin with blush and a makeup base that is a shade darker than you would normally use. Add definition to your eyebrows with a brow pencil, and use a yellow based concealer for under eye shadows. With the right makeup your gray hair will look fantastic, and you will actually look younger. [image style=" bordered" caption="" image_link="http://d1r5i20o8cadcu.cloudfront.net/designs/images/112839/original/_Group_0_-IMG_4565_IMG_4568-4_images-8_880px.jpg" /] Getting older doesn't mean you have to stop engaging in physical activities. In fact, exercise becomes even more critical as you begin to age. Although you may not be able to run as quickly as you did when you were younger or lift as much weight, there are many ways to incorporate a less vigorous fitness routine into your daily life. One of the simplest yet most beneficial exercises is to walk. If you enjoy the water, join a gym that has a pool. Do simple stretching exercises at home. Take a bike ride with your grandchildren. Look for ways to combine exercise with entertainment to maintain your health. Start taking care of your skin. The skin is the first place to show signs of aging since as it matures, aging spots appear and it becomes drier and loses elasticity. A good anti-aging moisturizer, however, can make your skin softer and reduce the appearance of existing wrinkles and help to delay the formation of new ones. Many older adults suffer with unsteadiness which is a normal part of aging. This can be caused by deterioration of connections between the nerves and muscles. Pick up loose rugs from the floors, wipe up spills or shower water quickly and try walking with a cane. One of the keys to aging healthily is to continue to find meaning in your life. For most people, life revolves around family and work, but as you grow older certain things may change, leaving a gap in your life. Children will leave the nest, and you will retire. This can suddenly leave you with a lot of spare time on your hands, but it doesn't mean that you should stop moving forward. In fact, it's the perfect time to find exciting new things to occupy your life. As we age, it is common to experience troubles with a leaky bladder. It can happen after a sneeze, laughter, or even coughing. As disheartening as it is, there are ways you can control a leaky bladder. See your doctor for tips on exercises you can do to strengthen the muscles that control bladder leakage. There are also medications that can help. As you can see, there are many ways you can help a loved one during the weeks and months following the death of a spouse. The best thing you can do is offer your help, in both practical and emotional ways. By using the tips we have offered, you can greatly ease the struggle during a most difficult time.
